SIMPLE: minstrelsy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Minstrelsy
<hw>Min"strel*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
arts and occupation of minstrels; the singing and playing of a
minstrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Musical instruments.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A collective body of minstrels, or musicians; also,
a collective body of minstrels' songs.</def> <au>Chaucer.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>minstrelsy</xex> of heaven.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mint</ent>⟦br⟧
